        "content": "<p>suppose you don't know these two numbers yet. you start from:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>1) n = 5s\n2) n = 13t\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>you want to prove that n is divisible by 65, so you multiply each one with the other, to obtain:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>3) 13n = 65s\n4) 5n = 65t\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(note that the two right hand sides already have 65 now)<br>\nnow if only I could combine these equations some way so that I get n in the LHS! so I want two magic numbers a and b such that:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>5) 13an = 65as\n6) 5bn = 65bt\n(5) - (6):\n(13a-5b)n = 65(as-bt)\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>so the property you want is 13a-5b = 1, so that the last equation just straight up tells you that n is divisible by 65!</p>",
